1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
The fury of nature continues to draw the landscape of the Canary Islands.

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:12,000
The volcanic eruption has just occurred on the island of La Palma.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Opening windows to the interior of the earth.

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:17,000
How deep it is.

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:25,000
A fracture that was left open from the eruption, in which you can still see incandescence.

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,000
With lethal environments.

7
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:31,000
There is a triple concentration of CO2 in the air.

8
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,000
This can cause death in a matter of seconds.

9
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Almost extraterrestrial.

10
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Under the permanent threat of new eruptions.

11
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:47,000
What would happen if an eruption occurred in the Teide?

12
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:49,000
We would not exist without volcanoes.

13
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,000
We have to learn to live with them.

14
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Canary Islands, Born of Fire.

15
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:59,000
Premieres Monday, September 12 at 10pm on National Geographic.

